quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  19,1,"Kaf, Ha, Ya, Ayn, Sad (These are the names of letters of the Arabic alphabet and only Allah knows their meaning here)"
  19,2,(This is) the mention of your Lord's mercy to His bondman Zakariyya (Zechariah)
  19,3,As he called out to his Lord a concealed call
  19,4,"He said, \"Lord! Surely the bone (s) within me have become feeble, and my head is turned white with hoary (hair) (Literally: is aflame with hoary \"hair\") and I have not been wretched in invoking you, Lord"
  19,5,"And surely I fear my patronized (relatives) beyond me, (i.e., after I am gone) and my wife is barren. So bestow upon me, from very close to You, a constant patron (Some take it to mean a nephew or kinsman)"
  19,6,"Who will inherit of me and inherit (also) of the house of Yaaqub; (Jacob) and make him, Lord, well satisfied"
  19,7,"O Zakariyya, surely We give you good tidings of a youth whose name is Yahya (John). No namesake have We given him earlier"
  19,8,"He said, \"Lord! However can I have a youth and my wife is barren, and I have already reached the decrepitude of old age"
  19,9,"He said, \"Thus (it will be) your Lord has said. Simple is it for Me, and I already created you, earlier, and you were nothing"
  19,10,"He said, \"Lord! Make for me (some) sign.\" Said He, \"Your sign is that you shall not speak to (any of) mankind, though being in perfect shape, (i.e. being without fault, or defect; literally: in \"perfect\" mold) three nights"
  19,11,"So he went out to his people from the Chamber, then he signified (Literally: revealed) to them, \"Extol (your Lord) before sunrise and at nightfall"